-- BOJ's Kuroda: moves in long term rates volatile, watching closely
-- 
-- Fri Apr 12, 2013 4:30am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/04/12/us-japan-economy-kuroda-idUSBRE93B09G20130412

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Bank of Japan Governor Haruhiko Kuroda said on Friday that since the bank overhauled monetary policy moves in long-term yields have been volatile and he wants to closely watch market moves. 
 Kuroda made the comments at a meeting on the government's monthly economic report, according to a Cabinet Office official. (Reporting by Stanley White; Editing by  Sanjeev Miglani )